args:
In order to prevent the return of the Progenitor,
the prince and his allies face off against Phares
and Beren, attempting to free the latter from
their enemy's machinations. The party then
finds themselves thrown into battle with the
＂terminals＂ called forth by the Progenitor.
The Alberian royals, hm? Maddening that\nyou should sniff us out, though I suppose\nI must acknowledge your prowess.
I imagine this means you're done imitating\nour poor brother Phares?
Oh, this is no imitation, Chelle. The one\nwho speaks to you now IS Phares.
He is merely influenced occasionally\nby my sacred will.
You are taking advantage of the man.\nThis is inexcusable.
And what would you do about it, mmm?
I will excise you from this world, and in\nso doing save not just my elder brother,\nbut Beren as well.
Save him? Ah, but you lack understanding.\nWithout my will, Phares remains dead.
And little Beren here is not some prisoner\nto my will, but is instead providing aid of\nhis own volition.
Have you ever given Beren a choice?\nAllowed him to think for himself?
Heh. Was it not you Alberian royals who\nnever gave him a choice?

Why, had I not released him, your dear
brother Beren would still be languishing
in the dark prison where your family left
him to be forgotten!
...Not our finest hour by any stretch,\nand we have much atoning to do for\nour part in it.
But all the more reason why we need\nto help Beren now.
You may well hate us, and you have the\nright; there is no excuse for our being\nunable to save you from your predicament.
But that is why we cannot leave you now.
Surely you must be aware of the fact\nyour mind remains caged even though\nyour body is now free?

I'll not preach brotherhood at this point,
but I also will not look away when one
who shares my dragonblood is being
used as a mindless tool.
Feel free to ignore this nonsense, Beren.\nYou are my right hand, and it is enough\nthat you serve to embody my will.

I have long felt that I am something
different from a common human. And it's
not about having power or being able to
do something odd. I'm just...different.
They claim I share dragonblood with their\nfamily, but does that make me the same\nas these people?
I don't know... I just don't know.\nSo what AM I?
Well, this is deeply fascinating. If Beren IS\nsome kind of special being, then by all\nmeans pray elucidate us on the matter.
There is no reason for me to answer you...\nBut seeing as Beren also wishes to know,\nI shall oblige.
You know of the Auspex, yes? I ask you,\nwhat manner of person do you think is\nchosen to serve as an Auspex?

You refer to Auspexes of the Ilian Church?
Well, if I recall correctly, they are people
who boast extraordinarily large amounts
of mana.
They also possess special mana which\nlets them communicate with other worlds.
But do you know how such people came\nto have the title of Auspex?
The name itself has no meaning; it was\nsomething Ilia selected on a whim.
Well, not Ilia exactly, but rather a faerie\nwho called herself Ilia and devoted herself\nto growing the Ilian Church.

You speak of Meene. It's a tale that could
well shake the foundations of Church
dogma. I wouldn't have believed it, but we
heard it from the Goddess herself...

Ah, good. Then I can dispense with some
of the backstory. As I was saying, the faerie
called Meene discovered a person with the
same special quality that Ilia possessed.

As Meene had personally experienced the
great destruction wrought by the Other,
she feared this quality might lead to the
same and attempted to control them.

By giving such people the title of Auspex
and installing them as individuals of great
import, it prevented them from leaving
the bounds of the Church.
So to sum up, Auspexes are individuals\nwho possess the same special quality\nas Ilia.
I'm assuming this ＂special quality＂ is\nsomething more than good looks and\na sparkling wit?
Indeed. It is a quality which makes them\nvessels of the Primal Mark.
Do you know why the dragons\ncontrol this world?
Because it is the way of things.

What you name ＂the way of things＂ was
instituted but a scant thousand years ago.
If considered from the genesis of this
world, that period is but an eyeblink.
All of it happened a thousand years ago,\nbrought about when Elysium took away\nthe Primal Mark that Ilia bore.
The Primal Mark is, so to speak, the\nauthority to control the world that was\npossessed by the Progenitor and Origin.
But once they were each no longer able to\ninterfere with the world, they bequeathed\ntheir Primal Marks unto others.
The Origin entrusted their Mark to Elysium,\nwhile the Progenitor made their Mark pass\nfrom person to person.

These people are the ones I speak of—
those who can contact other worlds and
who have the makeup to accept the
Primal Mark. They are...
It is said Auspexes can contact other\nworlds, but that is not strictly accurate.
Instead, they can contact the Progenitor.
They are but imitations—inferior copies\nthat the Progenitor made of themselves.
Then Auspexes are but copies\nof the Progenitor?
And Beren is just another vessel of the\nMark you created—one with the same\nAuspex qualities of Ilia and Zethia.
I know all about the Auspexes.\nBut I am different. I am not what they are.
If I were the same as them—if they were\nmy peers—then I wouldn't be like this!
Always alone, surrounded by nothing—\nyet drowning beneath it all the same!
You see it then, Beren. You see that you\nare different from the Auspexes, for they\ncan only peer into other worlds.

But you, Beren? You are the true vessel of
the Primal Mark. The one who can control
my power. The one I have eagerly awaited
for years beyond counting!

You think yourself different, and oh, how
correct you are. There is no being like you
in all of existence. In fact, there is only
one who is remotely the same...
And that is the Progenitor themselves.
So the only one like me is...\nthe Progenitor?

Correct. And if you understand that,
you will gather the miasma, create a
gateway for my return, and usher in
your one and only compatriot.
Listen to Chelle, Beren!\nNot the Progenitor!
Be quiet. I can't take it anymore. No one\nis the same as me. No one understands\nme—and I hate the world for that.
You're my brother, Beren,\nand that's not true at all!
Oh, look. The empty prince finally speaks.\nDo you have something you want to say\nto me, empty prince?
...You're right, Beren. I am empty.\nThat's why I understand how you feel.
I'm different from everyone else. Forget\nnot being a true prince—I'm not even a\ntrue human. I'm empty, just like you said.
When I learned that, I was afraid.\nI felt like I was going to be crushed\nbeneath the weight of that solitude.
So yes, Beren. I understand how you feel.
Then don't get in my way! What I need is\nsomeone JUST like me!
What made me understand—what saved\nme—was not someone just like me,\nbut instead the most normal of people.
Regular people, Beren! My friends!\nSo please, listen to us!
SHUT UP! I CAN'T STAND TO EVEN\nLOOK AT YOU!
Shut up! Shut up, shut up, shut up!
Enough! I'm going to end this! I'm going\nto kill you and be done with all this anger!
You focus on creating the gate. I will have\nmy terminals deal with this puppet.
Those are those dark cubes we've\noccasionally fought on the battlefield...\nSo THIS is where they come from!
Whatever they are, we need to deal with\nthem posthaste; each second we delay\ninvites the Progenitor's return!
We'll destroy whatever these confounded\nthings are and then stop Beren! Go!
